# Code Documentation Standards

Guidelines for documenting code throughout the codebase.

## Class Documentation

- Document all classes with a description of their purpose:
    ```typescript
    /**
     * Manages animations for characters with configurable animation sets
     */
    export class AnimationService {
    	// Implementation
    }
    ```

## Method Documentation

- Document public methods with descriptions, parameters, and return values:
    ```typescript
    /**
     * Plays an animation from the specified animation set
     * @param name The name of the animation set
     * @param fadeTime How long the animation takes to fade in (seconds)
     * @returns The AnimationTrack that was played
     */
    public playAnimation(name: string, fadeTime: number): AnimationTrack {
      // Implementation
    }
    ```

## Interface Documentation

- Document interfaces and their properties:
    ```typescript
    /**
     * Represents a character with required components
     */
    export interface Character extends Model {
    	/** The root part of the character used for positioning */
    	HumanoidRootPart: BasePart;
    	/** The humanoid component that controls the character */
    	Humanoid: Humanoid & {
    		Animator: Animator;
    	};
    }
    ```
